The paper proposes an algorithm for ad creative selection that considers the user's psychological status and wear-in/wear-out effects due to repetitive ad exposures. This involves machine learning and decision-making, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves information retrieval and optimization, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The user's psychological status and wear-in/wear-out effects also relate to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with online advertising, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
